   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recover COVID crisis for Ethnic Race in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project- RECOVER will recover COVID-19 crisis and disaster hazards, reduce vulnerability and reform livelihood and economic security of total 12000 COVID and disaster affected unemployed, extreme poor, ethnic and excluded people including 6532 poor fishermen, 4850 indigenous people, 495 excluded (Dalit) people and 128 LGBTI from 2000 targeted households in Uttar Sreepur and Dakshin Sreepur Unions, the remotest humanitarian settings of Tahirpur Upazila in Sunamganj District in  Bangladesh.</narrative>
  </description>
